{"parentUuid":"2f9d6daa-76aa-43a0-90f4-3da19444a397","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"96f7ce82-27af-4c04-ae02-270c4873a922","agentId":"a1cf23d1e97c4e687","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SADjHcS3ENr3Kt6qJrjqR8","type":"tool_result","content":"# Response\n\nI cannot locate the specific definition of \"Autonomous AI Research and Development\" Capability Threshold or its associated safeguard triggers in the provided PDF content.\n\nThe document appears to be Anthropic's \"Responsible Scaling Policy (version 2.2)\" based on the metadata, but the PDF content provided consists primarily of compressed/encoded image data and stream objects rather than readable text. While there are references to ASL (Anthropic Safety Level) frameworks and capability thresholds throughout the document structure, the actual definitions and specific threshold language are not accessible in the text portions provided.\n\nTo accurately quote the definitions and safeguard requirements you're asking about, I would need the document in a format where the text content is directly readable, rather than embedded in PDF image streams.\n\n[Binary content (application/pdf, 334.6KB) also saved to /Users/gg/.claude/projects/-Users-gg-Work-Yogi/d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f/tool-results/webfetch-1782027386946-uan5xl.pdf]"}]},"uuid":"417da20d-7b79-4878-abd2-b4aa15fb246c","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:31.959Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":342638,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Response\n\nI cannot locate the specific definition of \"Autonomous AI Research and Development\" Capability Threshold or its associated safeguard triggers in the provided PDF content.\n\nThe document appears to be Anthropic's \"Responsible Scaling Policy (version 2.2)\" based on the metadata, but the PDF content provided consists primarily of compressed/encoded image data and stream objects rather than readable text. While there are references to ASL (Anthropic Safety Level) frameworks and capability thresholds throughout the document structure, the actual definitions and specific threshold language are not accessible in the text portions provided.\n\nTo accurately quote the definitions and safeguard requirements you're asking about, I would need the document in a format where the text content is directly readable, rather than embedded in PDF image streams.\n\n[Binary content (application/pdf, 334.6KB) also saved to /Users/gg/.claude/projects/-Users-gg-Work-Yogi/d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f/tool-results/webfetch-1782027386946-uan5xl.pdf]","durationMs":5117,"url":"https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/872c653b2d0501d6ab44cf87f43e1dc4853e4d37.pdf"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2f9d6daa-76aa-43a0-90f4-3da19444a397","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"5c828542-67b8-4e27-a709-c8a762c27127","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"96f7ce82-27af-4c04-ae02-270c4873a922","agentId":"a1cf23d1e97c4e687","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WZt1u5mTCBgTB2v5PAfkbu","type":"tool_result","content":"# AI R&D and Autonomous Capabilities as Dangerous Thresholds\n\n## Tracked Threat Models\n\nMultiple frontier AI safety policies explicitly treat automated AI R&D as a catastrophic risk threshold:\n\n**Anthropic's policy identifies:**\n\"AI R&D-4: The ability to fully automate the work of an entry-level, remote-only Researcher at Anthropic.\"\n\n**OpenAI's framework defines Critical capability as:**\n\"The model is capable of recursively self improving (i.e., fully automated AI R&D)\"\n\n**Google DeepMind recognizes:**\n\"Machine Learning R&D: Risks of the misuse of models capable of accelerating the rate of AI progress\"\n\n**Magic's policy states:**\n\"The model facilitates a dramatic acceleration in the rate of effective compute scaling or can effectively replace high-level machine learning researchers.\"\n\n## Associated Mitigations\n\nPolicies tie specific containment and deployment restrictions to these thresholds:\n\n- **Google DeepMind** recommends Security Level 3-4 for ML R&D capabilities, involving restricted access and hardened environments\n- **Microsoft** requires that models fully automating the AI R&D pipeline trigger \"Critical\" risk designation with highest-level safeguards\n- **Meta** accounts for \"automated AI R&D\" as an enabling capability during evaluations that increases potential for harm\n\nThe policies establish that self-improving or researcher-replacing capabilities require security measures preventing unauthorized access and strict limitations on external deployment."}]},"uuid":"c9310634-5fc3-4636-9557-be9735b5d72e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:38.192Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":327573,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# AI R&D and Autonomous Capabilities as Dangerous Thresholds\n\n## Tracked Threat Models\n\nMultiple frontier AI safety policies explicitly treat automated AI R&D as a catastrophic risk threshold:\n\n**Anthropic's policy identifies:**\n\"AI R&D-4: The ability to fully automate the work of an entry-level, remote-only Researcher at Anthropic.\"\n\n**OpenAI's framework defines Critical capability as:**\n\"The model is capable of recursively self improving (i.e., fully automated AI R&D)\"\n\n**Google DeepMind recognizes:**\n\"Machine Learning R&D: Risks of the misuse of models capable of accelerating the rate of AI progress\"\n\n**Magic's policy states:**\n\"The model facilitates a dramatic acceleration in the rate of effective compute scaling or can effectively replace high-level machine learning researchers.\"\n\n## Associated Mitigations\n\nPolicies tie specific containment and deployment restrictions to these thresholds:\n\n- **Google DeepMind** recommends Security Level 3-4 for ML R&D capabilities, involving restricted access and hardened environments\n- **Microsoft** requires that models fully automating the AI R&D pipeline trigger \"Critical\" risk designation with highest-level safeguards\n- **Meta** accounts for \"automated AI R&D\" as an enabling capability during evaluations that increases potential for harm\n\nThe policies establish that self-improving or researcher-replacing capabilities require security measures preventing unauthorized access and strict limitations on external deployment.","durationMs":8641,"url":"https://metr.org/common-elements"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5c828542-67b8-4e27-a709-c8a762c27127","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
